com.apriori.possible

Interface Possible<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the possible value
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Fulfillable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Holder, Reference

    public interface Possible<T>
    A possible value. A value might be present, but it may not be. This interface provides basically the same API as Optional, but as an interface instead of a class. Other implementations are provided in this package, including ones that allow present null values and ones that are mutable.

      • fromFuture

        static <T> Possible<T> fromFuture(Future<? extends T> future)
        Returns a view of a future as a possible value. If the future is incomplete, fails, or is cancelled then the value is not present. If and when the future completes successfully, the value will become present. The actual value is the future's result.
        Parameters:
        future - the future
        Returns:
        a view of the future as a Possible

      • presentOnly

        static <T> List<T> presentOnly(Collection<? extends Possible<T>> possibles)
        Returns a list of the present values from the specified collection of possible values. Possible values where no value is present are excluded. So the resulting list will have fewer elements than the specified collection in the event that not all values are present. The order of items in the list matches the iteration order of the specified collection.
        Parameters:
        possibles - a collection of possible values
        Returns:
        a list of present values

      • nullIfNotPresent

        static <T> List<T> nullIfNotPresent(Collection<? extends Possible<T>> possibles)
        Returns a list of the values, null if no value is present, from the specified collection of possible values. The resulting list will always have exactly the same number of elements as the specified collection, even if not all values are present. The order of items in the list matches the iteration order of the specified collection.
        Parameters:
        possibles - a collection of possible values
        Returns:
        a list of values extracted from the collection, null for objects where a value was not present

      • snapshot

        static <T> Possible<T> snapshot(Possible<T> possible)
        Captures the current possible value into a new immutable possible value. The returned object is an immutable copy of the specified value. If the specified object is mutable and later changes, those changes will not be reflected in the returned snapshot.
        Parameters:
        possible - a possible value
        Returns:
        an immutable snapshot of the possible value
